  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This model is developed iteratively, firstly during &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../soa.rup_soma/tasks/soa_goal_service_assignment_46A9906C.html&quot; guid=&quot;_I7P6gCwTEduKcvYAyaKSaA&quot;>Task:&#xD;
    Identify and Associate Services to Goals&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;the model includes all candidate services mapped to the business&#xD;
    strategy in terms of business goals. During &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../soa.rup_soma/tasks/soa_service_qualification_E0D920A6.html&quot; guid=&quot;_mHhK8CwUEduKcvYAyaKSaA&quot;>Task: Apply&#xD;
    Services Litmus Tests&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;service exposure decisions are taken and so the mapping of exposed services must be&#xD;
    checked and if necessary refined to ensure that the details are correct. An instance of the Goal-Service model should&#xD;
    address all business domains that are within the scope of the project.&amp;nbsp; It is preferable to create a single&#xD;
    Goal-Service Model instance for the project, rather than one per domain.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This work product may be represented in a number of ways, described below, the manner of its representation is far less&#xD;
    important than the fact that its information has to be kept up-to-date as the details of the service model change.&#xD;
    Therefore it is common for this model to be represented in a form that facilitates rapid review and change.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <keyConsiderations>The Goal Service Model is required to ensure traceability between the Business Strategy and IT Capabilities; it supports&#xD;
accountability in the relationship between the business and IT and as such must be kept up to date.</keyConsiderations>
  <purpose>The goal service model is used to ensure direct relationships between the business goals, as an articulation of the&#xD;
business strategy, and the services which represent the IT capabilities provided to the business to meet the stated goals.&#xD;
This model is therefore a capture of the traceability between Business Strategy and IT Capabilities.</purpose>
  <impactOfNotHaving>Without this artifact, in one of its forms, there is no traceability and therefore no accountability between the business&#xD;
expression of strategy and need and the IT systems developed to support the business.</impactOfNotHaving>
  <reasonsForNotNeeding>Where services are developed purely to provide infrastructure capabilities it may be possible to dispense with this model&#xD;
as there are no business strategy items being supported by such services.</reasonsForNotNeeding>
  <representationOptions>&lt;p>&#xD;
    UML Representation:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        A Model, stereotyped &amp;lt;&amp;lt;Goal Service Model&amp;gt;&amp;gt; containing the set of &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_goal_D99D08F9.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{6DC6732B-E7F1-495E-B5EC-AEBFD7BE80FE}&quot;>Artifact: Business Goal&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;and &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../soa.rup_soma/workproducts/soa_svce_model_svce_spec_37E89A91.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{20F06B5E-95D5-422C-AB68-7C213D28533A}&quot;>Artifact: Service Specification&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;and their dependencies that&#xD;
        constitute the goal service model.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Requirements Representation:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        As an &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot; href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_goal_D99D08F9.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{6DC6732B-E7F1-495E-B5EC-AEBFD7BE80FE}&quot;>Artifact: Business Goal&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;may be considered as a requirement&#xD;
        for IT Capabilities to support, it is therefore possible to capture the business strategy in a requirements tools,&#xD;
        as described in &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/guidances/toolmentors/identify_biz_goals_reqpro_39C8E504.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_htCiQCyZEdu4Col-dmm97w&quot;>Tool Mentor: Identify Business Goals Using Rational RequisitePro&lt;/a>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
